brand: replace stacked-tile mark with new gradient "A" app icon

- New logo (Nano Banana / Gemini): squircle tile in the site's
  indigo→violet→fuchsia gradient with a clean white "A" monogram and
  the existing gold "live" accent dot baked in. Saved at
  public/brand-logo.png and app/icon.png so Next auto-serves it as
  favicon.
- BrandMark rewritten to render the PNG via next/image while keeping
  the existing prop API (size / tone / static / className), so every
  call site (Hero, splash loader, etc.) keeps working untouched. Outer
  fuchsia halo preserves the "live" pulse without animating the icon.
- HomeSplashLoader: dropped the redundant gradient wrapper + inner
  ring around the mark — the new icon is a self-contained tile, so
  the wrapper was double-stacking gradients. Bumped splash mark to
  72px and kept the soft halo ripple.
